<section class="overview">

<div class="container">

<h2>What is a Medical Device?</h2>

<p>

A medical device is any instrument, apparatus, machine, implant,
software, material, reagent or related article intended by the
manufacturer to be used for human beings for medical purposes.

Unlike medicines, medical devices primarily achieve their intended
purpose through physical, mechanical or software-based means rather
than pharmacological action.

Medical devices range from simple products such as thermometers and
syringes to highly sophisticated robotic surgical systems,
implantable pacemakers and artificial intelligence powered diagnostic
software.

</p>

</div>

</section>

<section class="cards">

<div class="container">

<h2>Examples of Medical Devices</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>🩺 Diagnostic Devices</h3>

<ul>

<li>Thermometer</li>

<li>ECG Machine</li>

<li>MRI Scanner</li>

<li>CT Scanner</li>

<li>Ultrasound</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>💉 Therapeutic Devices</h3>

<ul>

<li>Infusion Pump</li>

<li>Dialysis Machine</li>

<li>Ventilator</li>

<li>Defibrillator</li>

<li>Laser System</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>🦴 Implantable Devices</h3>

<ul>

<li>Total Hip Implant</li>

<li>Knee Implant</li>

<li>Dental Implant</li>

<li>Pacemaker</li>

<li>Heart Valve</li>

</ul>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>
<section class="classification">

<div class="container">

<h2>Medical Device Classification</h2>

<p>

Medical devices are classified according to the level of risk posed to
patients and users. Higher risk devices require greater regulatory
control, clinical evidence and post-market monitoring.

</p>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>Class A</h3>

<p><strong>Low Risk</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Bandages</li>
<li>Surgical Gloves</li>
<li>Tongue Depressors</li>
<li>Wheelchairs</li>
</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Class B</h3>

<p><strong>Low–Moderate Risk</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Hypodermic Needles</li>
<li>Suction Equipment</li>
<li>Infusion Pumps</li>
<li>Dental Filling Materials</li>
</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Class C</h3>

<p><strong>Moderate–High Risk</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Ventilators</li>
<li>Bone Plates</li>
<li>Orthopedic Implants</li>
<li>Hemodialysis Equipment</li>
</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Class D</h3>

<p><strong>High Risk</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Heart Valves</li>
<li>Pacemakers</li>
<li>Drug Eluting Stents</li>
<li>Artificial Heart Devices</li>
</ul>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

