<section class="documents">

<div class="container">

<h2>Important Regulatory Documents</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">
<h3>📄 Device Master File (DMF)</h3>
<p>
Contains complete technical documentation of a medical device including
design, manufacturing, testing, labeling and regulatory information.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>⚠ Risk Management File</h3>
<p>
Prepared according to ISO 14971 and includes hazard identification,
risk analysis, risk control and residual risk evaluation.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>📊 Clinical Evaluation Report (CER)</h3>
<p>
Demonstrates clinical safety and performance using clinical evidence,
literature review and post-market information.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>📈 Post Market Surveillance (PMS)</h3>
<p>
Continuous monitoring of product safety and performance after market
release.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>📋 Design History File (DHF)</h3>
<p>
Contains complete records generated during design and development of
the medical device.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>📝 Instructions for Use (IFU)</h3>
<p>
Provides safe operating instructions, warnings, precautions and
device information for users.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="career">

<div class="container">

<h2>Career Opportunities</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">
<h3>Regulatory Affairs</h3>
<p>
Preparation of technical documentation, regulatory submissions,
DMF, CER and compliance activities.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Quality Assurance</h3>
<p>
ISO 13485 implementation, CAPA, Internal Audit, SOPs and Quality
Management Systems.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Research & Development</h3>
<p>
Medical device design, prototyping, verification and validation.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Clinical Affairs</h3>
<p>
Clinical investigations, PMCF, CER preparation and literature review.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="faq">

<div class="container">

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">
<h3>What is a Medical Device?</h3>
<p>
A product intended for diagnosis, prevention, monitoring, treatment or
alleviation of disease without achieving its primary intended action
through pharmacological means.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Which ISO standard is most important?</h3>
<p>
ISO 13485 forms the foundation of Quality Management Systems for
medical device manufacturers, supported by ISO 14971 and other
applicable standards.
</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Who regulates Medical Devices?</h3>
<p>
Authorities such as CDSCO, FDA, EU MDR authorities, MHRA, TGA and
Health Canada regulate medical devices in their respective regions.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

